1)What is Ansible?
-- It’s an automation platform which helps in provisioning, configuring, deploying and network automation.
--Tool used is widely for configure   management.
--Follows push mechanism
--Agent less(software)
--Yaml language(simple) 
--Idempotent(Performing an operation repeatedly without changing the outcome after the first time)

2)Playbooks:
 -- It’s a text file written in YAML language that 
 tells ansible what to do. 

3)Control and Manage nodes:
--Control node: VM in which Ansible is  installed.   
--Manage node: VM which is used to manage configuration.

